1
00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:08,320
Chen.

2
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:09,800
It's me, Wang Li.

3
00:00:10,350 --> 00:00:12,240
Can you lend me money one last time?

4
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:13,400
Just…

5
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:14,960
Hello?

6
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:28,030
Sorry, the number you dialed

7
00:00:28,030 --> 00:00:29,350
is currently unavailable.

8
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,440
Ali.

9
00:00:34,390 --> 00:00:36,430
You know my mom's condition.

10
00:00:38,320 --> 00:00:39,320
Her medicine can't stop.

11
00:00:40,470 --> 00:00:41,520
My salary…

12
00:00:48,110 --> 00:00:48,950
Don't worry.

13
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:56,000
I won't owe you life-saving money.

14
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:09,900
(Mr. Wang: Old friend, let's meet tonight.)

15
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:19,660
(Mr. Wang: Old friend, let's meet tonight.)

16
00:01:31,140 --> 00:01:32,780
(Pay Up)

17
00:01:32,790 --> 00:01:33,870
It's a mess here.

18
00:01:34,790 --> 00:01:36,350
- I got it, I got it.
- It's fine.

19
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:37,400
I'll have them clean up.

20
00:01:38,120 --> 00:01:38,960
Sit.

21
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:50,760
I borrowed from a lot of people.

22
00:01:52,950 --> 00:01:54,790
You're the only one who helped.

23
00:01:56,230 --> 00:01:57,230
We were classmates.

24
00:01:58,040 --> 00:01:59,350
I know things haven't been easy.

25
00:02:01,710 --> 00:02:03,710
I know it's not easy for you.

26
00:02:06,310 --> 00:02:08,120
Your daughter got sick so young.

27
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,190
I really had no choice.

28
00:02:13,190 --> 00:02:14,030
Bai,

29
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,520
you lending me the money

30
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:19,310
means saving my daughter's life.

31
00:02:22,430 --> 00:02:24,840
Whatever you want me to do, I'll do it.

32
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:28,680
My daughter and I will be grateful forever.

33
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:32,640
I get it.

34
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:35,710
I really do.

35
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,590
Look.

36
00:02:38,430 --> 00:02:41,470
But the surgery costs too much.

37
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:42,750
I know.

38
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:44,750
Bai, how much can you lend me?

39
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,360
Just say it.

40
00:02:46,360 --> 00:02:48,310
I'll figure out the rest.

41
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,150
Same as you.

42
00:02:50,870 --> 00:02:52,750
I'm tight on cash right now.

43
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:54,800
What do you mean?

44
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:56,310
You said on the phone

45
00:02:57,430 --> 00:02:58,430
it wouldn't be a problem,

46
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:00,840
that you had a way?

47
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:02,280
Right.

48
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:07,590
But saving your daughter

49
00:03:08,190 --> 00:03:09,120
depends on you.

50
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:10,630
On me?

51
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,200
What do you mean?

52
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:15,000
Lately, I've been thinking

53
00:03:15,750 --> 00:03:17,470
about running a banquet business.

54
00:03:18,120 --> 00:03:20,150
You own a restaurant.

55
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:21,470
We work together.

56
00:03:21,870 --> 00:03:23,000
If it goes well,

57
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,800
not just the surgery,

58
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,470
your daughter will be set

59
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:29,680
for the rest of her life.

60
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:38,740
=The Hidden Truth=

61
00:03:38,740 --> 00:03:41,380
=Episode 4=

62
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:50,280
You must be Yimo.

63
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:53,430
You've grown so much.

64
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:02,590
You're Mr. Bai, right?

65
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:07,870
I saw my dad's graduation photo.

66
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,710
You were in it.

67
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,590
(Graduation Photo)
It's written on the back.

68
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:13,080
Bai Qiming.

69
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:15,240
Yeah.

70
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:17,560
I've been working

71
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,750
out of town these years.

72
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:20,270
Just got back.

73
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,000
I remember

74
00:04:22,310 --> 00:04:24,310
you were only this much taller

75
00:04:25,310 --> 00:04:26,310
than the table.

76
00:04:27,960 --> 00:04:29,000
And in the blink of an eye,

77
00:04:30,510 --> 00:04:31,800
you're such a big girl now.

78
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:34,760
Yimo,

79
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:37,310
I'm talking business with Bai.

80
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:38,480
You head back first.

81
00:04:39,950 --> 00:04:41,430
We've covered everything.

82
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,160
Nothing else.

83
00:04:43,430 --> 00:04:46,070
I won't disturb you.

84
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,800
Seeing you both doing well

85
00:04:52,920 --> 00:04:54,430
puts my mind at ease.

86
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,440
Yimo,

87
00:05:06,120 --> 00:05:07,680
next time I'll treat your dad to dinner.

88
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:09,950
You should come too.

89
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:45,840
Hungry?

90
00:05:46,280 --> 00:05:47,460
I'll cook.

91
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,560
I'm not hungry.

92
00:06:00,950 --> 00:06:01,790
Dad.

93
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:12,190
Light bulb's out again.

94
00:06:30,540 --> 00:06:31,440
Dad,

95
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:35,070
what was Mr. Bai

96
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:37,000
here for today?

97
00:06:38,070 --> 00:06:39,510
You didn't look so good.

98
00:06:39,720 --> 00:06:41,310
Business disagreement.

99
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:42,270
Normal stuff.

100
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:45,830
It'll be resolved soon.

101
00:06:48,070 --> 00:06:48,910
Dad,

102
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,800
I was too young before.

103
00:06:50,950 --> 00:06:52,270
I couldn't help.

104
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:54,750
But now I'm grown.

105
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,920
If there's anything,

106
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,630
I can share the burden with you.

107
00:06:57,950 --> 00:06:59,480
My daughter really has grown up.

108
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:01,960
But, hey,

109
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,000
don't worry.

110
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:08,040
I can handle it.

111
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:12,310
Dad, I trust you.

112
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,800
But you have to trust me too.

113
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:17,360
I'm the one closest to you.

114
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:19,510
You can tell me anything.

115
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,870
About Mr. Bai,

116
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:31,000
we were classmates,

117
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,480
but we haven't seen each other in years.

118
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:35,560
He left a long time ago

119
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:37,600
and suddenly came back.

120
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:41,360
I really don't know him anymore.

121
00:07:43,190 --> 00:07:44,920
If you run into him,

122
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:48,190
and he says anything to you,

123
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:49,950
tell me right away.

124
00:07:50,830 --> 00:07:52,070
Sound him out for me.

125
00:07:52,920 --> 00:07:54,000
In business,

126
00:07:54,160 --> 00:07:55,120
even with old friends,

127
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,430
you have to stay alert.

128
00:08:00,310 --> 00:08:01,150
Okay.

129
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,310
But why would he look for me anyway?

130
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:06,440
Dad,

131
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,120
if you're this worried,

132
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,480
I might as well not go anywhere.

133
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:10,750
You can tie me to your belt

134
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:12,190
and watch me all day.

135
00:08:19,120 --> 00:08:19,960
Oh, by the way,

136
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:23,000
Officer Tang came by the restaurant today.

137
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:26,270
He seems to care about you.

138
00:08:27,630 --> 00:08:29,190
Dad, no.

139
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:31,600
Officer Tang's helped me a lot.

140
00:08:31,750 --> 00:08:33,240
It's not what you think.

141
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,000
Honestly, I think he's a good guy.

142
00:08:35,630 --> 00:08:36,600
He's a cop.

143
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:38,390
With him around you,

144
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,870
I feel at ease.

145
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:44,200
I hope you spend more time

146
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:45,840
with him.

147
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,280
Dad.

148
00:09:12,870 --> 00:09:13,710
Who is it?

149
00:09:15,320 --> 00:09:17,120
- Who?
- Ali, it's me.

150
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:22,550
Ms. Tong.

151
00:09:22,550 --> 00:09:23,390
Yimo.

152
00:09:23,510 --> 00:09:25,270
You made food for my dad again?

153
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,790
It's for you.

154
00:09:28,120 --> 00:09:29,510
Your dad's just tagging along.

155
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:31,480
I'll put it in the fridge.

156
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,390
For breakfast tomorrow.

157
00:09:32,390 --> 00:09:33,230
Alright.

158
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:40,840
You look tired.

159
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,320
It's okay.

160
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:45,320
Just busy at the restaurant.

161
00:09:46,670 --> 00:09:49,080
Dad's got secrets now.

162
00:09:49,670 --> 00:09:50,600
Nonsense.

163
00:09:50,910 --> 00:09:52,550
Dad, since your friend is here,

164
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:53,670
I'll leave you to it.

165
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,200
Stay.

166
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,320
Your dad says

167
00:09:57,390 --> 00:09:58,440
you've been helping

168
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:00,480
since you came back.

169
00:10:00,540 --> 00:10:01,550
Not a day off.

170
00:10:01,550 --> 00:10:03,080
This weekend,

171
00:10:03,550 --> 00:10:05,440
I'll take you shopping.

172
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:06,560
Sure.

173
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,600
But give me a couple days.

174
00:10:08,750 --> 00:10:09,670
You two chat.

175
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:10,790
I'll go to my room.

176
00:10:10,790 --> 00:10:12,600
I won't disturb your 'alone time'.

177
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:15,390
What alone time?

178
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:17,510
Your daughter

179
00:10:17,510 --> 00:10:19,390
is just like you.

180
00:10:20,030 --> 00:10:20,870
That she is.

181
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:27,940
(Hongyun Restaurant)

182
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,160
Xiaoqian.

183
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:37,750
Yimo, you're really back.

184
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:38,800
Hello, Mr. Wang.

185
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:41,120
Last month I saw someone on the street

186
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:42,270
who looked just like you.

187
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,870
You were vague in your messages.

188
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,270
What did you want to talk about?

189
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:49,790
Don't just stand out here,

190
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,840
come inside and talk.

191
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:52,390
I'll go ahead.

192
00:10:58,910 --> 00:11:01,000
Yimo, I...

193
00:11:01,030 --> 00:11:02,120
Let's talk inside.

194
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,080
Okay.

195
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:08,800
Sit.

196
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:13,800
What's wrong?

197
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:17,030
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

198
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,150
I got scammed.

199
00:11:29,150 --> 00:11:31,030
Days ago, I was setting up my livestream,

200
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,390
and there was an order.

201
00:11:34,030 --> 00:11:35,600
The buyer was from the south.

202
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:37,360
We chatted.

203
00:11:38,440 --> 00:11:39,280
And then…

204
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,150
What happened?

205
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,390
He said my DIY jewelry looked great

206
00:11:45,450 --> 00:11:46,390
and wanted me to supply

207
00:11:46,390 --> 00:11:47,360
so he could distribute.

208
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:50,360
The order size was huge.

209
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:51,840
I wanted to turn it down.

210
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:53,200
But he just

211
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:55,120
sent the deposit right away.

212
00:11:55,540 --> 00:11:56,390
I thought

213
00:11:56,390 --> 00:11:59,080
it was a stable way to make money.

214
00:11:59,080 --> 00:12:00,200
So I accepted.

215
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:01,910
That sounds good.

216
00:12:02,150 --> 00:12:03,080
He paid.

217
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:05,000
You just fulfill the order.

218
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,150
I got excited

219
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:07,790
and ordered materials

220
00:12:07,790 --> 00:12:08,960
and paid everything upfront.

221
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:12,030
When I checked the backend this morning,

222
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:14,390
it was canceled.

223
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:16,430
He didn't even want the deposit.

224
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:17,630
He vanished.

225
00:12:20,790 --> 00:12:21,960
Did you call the police?

226
00:12:22,670 --> 00:12:23,510
I did.

227
00:12:24,270 --> 00:12:25,120
They said

228
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:27,720
the account was overseas

229
00:12:27,720 --> 00:12:29,120
and already shut down.

230
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,320
No way to track him.

231
00:12:33,510 --> 00:12:35,440
How much did you order?

232
00:12:37,270 --> 00:12:38,120
Over 200,000.

233
00:12:40,550 --> 00:12:41,840
Some of it was borrowed.

234
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,390
That was all the money I had.

235
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:48,390
And I've spent it all.

236
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:54,870
Can't you refund online orders?

237
00:12:55,010 --> 00:12:56,030
It's been a short time,

238
00:12:56,030 --> 00:12:57,720
you should be able to return it, right?

239
00:12:57,750 --> 00:12:58,590
Normally yes.

240
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,000
But I contacted

241
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,360
my suppliers privately.

242
00:13:03,510 --> 00:13:05,390
We've worked together for years.

243
00:13:05,390 --> 00:13:06,960
It was cheaper than online.

244
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,510
When I asked

245
00:13:08,510 --> 00:13:10,790
for refunds this morning,

246
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:12,600
they refused.

247
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:14,600
The police said

248
00:13:14,670 --> 00:13:16,360
it was a legal transaction.

249
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:18,150
Nothing they could do.

250
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:19,790
That was careless.

251
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:21,030
You should never

252
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,550
transfer money privately.

253
00:13:22,550 --> 00:13:23,550
I didn't want to.

254
00:13:23,550 --> 00:13:25,200
I just wanted to make money.

255
00:13:25,270 --> 00:13:27,270
Who knew I'd meet a scammer?

256
00:13:28,670 --> 00:13:29,600
I'm sorry.

257
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:30,910
I didn't mean it like that.

258
00:13:33,270 --> 00:13:35,080
I'll think of a way.

259
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,510
We'll solve it.

260
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:40,390
Did you tell your family?

261
00:13:40,910 --> 00:13:41,870
I was too scared.

262
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,870
My dad's been sick for years.

263
00:13:43,870 --> 00:13:45,240
There's no money at home.

264
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:47,030
That's why I was so desperate

265
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:48,270
to make money.

266
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:50,390
I even took online loans for the materials.

267
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:53,270
Yimo, help me.

268
00:13:55,720 --> 00:13:57,550
I just got back.

269
00:13:57,670 --> 00:13:59,030
I don't have money either.

270
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:03,120
You gotta help me figure it out.

271
00:14:04,870 --> 00:14:06,360
I'm really out of options.

272
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:08,030
I don't know who else to turn to.

273
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:09,720
Don't worry.

274
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,200
Let me think.

275
00:14:21,550 --> 00:14:24,270
I do have an idea.

276
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:26,240
But...

277
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,360
Don't "but".

278
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:29,750
Just tell me.

279
00:14:30,790 --> 00:14:32,120
I have a classmate.

280
00:14:32,390 --> 00:14:35,240
He might have a powerful brother.

281
00:14:36,670 --> 00:14:38,270
I need to ask first.

282
00:14:39,030 --> 00:14:40,000
That works.

283
00:14:40,030 --> 00:14:41,150
Please ask him.

284
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,240
As long as it gets solved,

285
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:43,550
I'll thank him any way I can.

286
00:14:43,670 --> 00:14:45,360
Okay. I'll call him.

287
00:14:57,790 --> 00:14:58,630
Is this the place?

288
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,200
Let's go.

289
00:15:07,510 --> 00:15:08,750
You're here. Have a seat.

290
00:15:16,670 --> 00:15:17,510
Yimo?

291
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:18,560
Hello, Li Xu.

292
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:20,600
Xiaoqian?

293
00:15:20,910 --> 00:15:21,750
Yes.

294
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:24,390
How did this happen?

295
00:15:24,480 --> 00:15:25,960
You actually got scammed?

296
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:27,630
You know,

297
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:30,550
I hate scammers more than anything.

298
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,000
At a time like this,

299
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,910
there are still people pulling this crap.

300
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:36,870
Don't worry.

301
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:38,630
Since the call came to me,

302
00:15:38,630 --> 00:15:40,240
I can't just ignore it.

303
00:15:40,390 --> 00:15:41,750
You're here now.

304
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,870
Put your hearts at ease.

305
00:15:44,080 --> 00:15:45,030
Tonight's on me.

306
00:15:45,030 --> 00:15:46,630
We'll have a simple meal.

307
00:15:46,630 --> 00:15:48,240
Calm your nerves.

308
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:52,240
Still scared?

309
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,390
Don't be.

310
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:55,750
Once it's with me,

311
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:57,440
it's not a problem.

312
00:15:57,670 --> 00:15:58,510
Relax.

313
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:00,320
Thank you.

314
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:03,630
We'll repay you little by little.

315
00:16:04,020 --> 00:16:05,120
What are you talking about?

316
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:06,790
You're very welcome.

317
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:08,120
You don't need to.

318
00:16:08,270 --> 00:16:09,630
Make yourselves at home.

319
00:16:09,630 --> 00:16:10,790
Come, have some tea.

320
00:16:10,790 --> 00:16:11,630
Thanks.

321
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,440
Excuse us. We'll have a quick word.

322
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:23,840
Sure.

323
00:16:28,630 --> 00:16:30,030
You've already helped me a lot.

324
00:16:30,270 --> 00:16:31,750
I'll handle the rest.

325
00:16:32,020 --> 00:16:32,880
You should go.

326
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,240
I'll stay with you.

327
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,440
It doesn't feel safe here.

328
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,280
You go first.

329
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:38,390
I'll stay for dinner

330
00:16:39,270 --> 00:16:40,550
and talk things through.

331
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:44,360
Sorry, Li Xu.

332
00:16:44,550 --> 00:16:46,390
My friend don't want to trouble you.

333
00:16:46,390 --> 00:16:48,320
She's not staying for dinner,

334
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:50,510
and her dad wants her home tonight.

335
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:53,390
How about I stay and eat with you?

336
00:16:53,550 --> 00:16:55,360
- What do you say?
- That's fine.

337
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:57,670
You can just say it openly.

338
00:16:57,670 --> 00:16:58,960
If you both have things to do,

339
00:16:58,960 --> 00:16:59,890
you can leave.

340
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:00,820
We'll meet another day.

341
00:17:00,830 --> 00:17:01,960
No, I'm fine.

342
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:03,200
Li Xu,

343
00:17:04,270 --> 00:17:06,200
I'll walk my friend out

344
00:17:06,350 --> 00:17:07,510
and come back.

345
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:08,760
Alright.

346
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,270
Thank you, Li Xu.

347
00:17:21,070 --> 00:17:24,200
It's the shopping street challenge.

348
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:26,510
Put your hands up.

349
00:17:26,590 --> 00:17:27,590
Alright, guys.

350
00:17:27,590 --> 00:17:28,830
This is Dalong and Xiaohu.

351
00:17:28,830 --> 00:17:29,880
Yeah, just the two of us.

352
00:17:29,880 --> 00:17:30,790
Got a fan here.

353
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,880
Hey everyone, hit follow.

354
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:33,720
(Dalong and Xiaohu)
Follow us.

355
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:34,790
- Live streaming?
- Yeah.

356
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:37,000
Family, got gifts? Send gifts.

357
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:38,640
No gifts? Drop a fan badge.

358
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,270
At least tap some hearts.

359
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:41,640
Ms. Wang's here.

360
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:43,160
Thanks for the hot-air balloon.

361
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,830
Thank you.

362
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:46,640
Dalong bows to you.

363
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,030
Thank you.

364
00:17:49,070 --> 00:17:50,070
Stop it.

365
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:52,400
Why?

366
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:55,240
Stop. Turn around.

367
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:56,480
There's a thief.

368
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:58,350
Put it down.

369
00:17:58,880 --> 00:17:59,720
Drop it.

370
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:01,950
Stop.

371
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,000
Stop it.

372
00:18:04,640 --> 00:18:05,590
Stop running.

373
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:06,800
Stop it.

374
00:18:08,310 --> 00:18:09,270
Stop right there.

375
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:11,280
Stop.

376
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,520
Stop it.

377
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:14,910
Get him.

378
00:18:15,440 --> 00:18:17,000
He's getting away. Somebody help.

379
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:27,880
Stop! Don't run!

380
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:29,160
Get him! Get him!

381
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,800
Stop right there.

382
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:31,920
That phone thief!

383
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:33,160
Don't run!

384
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,160
He's fast!

385
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:35,110
Block him!

386
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:38,720
Catch the thief! My phone!

387
00:18:44,270 --> 00:18:46,750
Look. Those two are kinda funny.

388
00:18:47,200 --> 00:18:49,510
Fake. It's all scripted.

389
00:18:49,510 --> 00:18:50,790
Let's eat.

390
00:18:50,790 --> 00:18:53,480
- Eat.
- Come on. Dig in.

391
00:19:02,310 --> 00:19:04,070
You two done showing off?

392
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:05,880
Shut the stream off. Now.

393
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,280
Stop there.

394
00:19:30,110 --> 00:19:32,680
Gentlemen, welcome.

395
00:19:34,790 --> 00:19:35,630
Alright.

396
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:41,930
Xiaohu.

397
00:19:42,590 --> 00:19:44,400
I don't think we're earth signs.

398
00:19:44,550 --> 00:19:46,310
'Cause we're on fire.

399
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:49,000
You're wood, and I'm fire.

400
00:19:49,350 --> 00:19:50,550
We burn strong together.

401
00:19:51,830 --> 00:19:55,030
Our fire was pretty weak before.

402
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:57,480
We keep fueling each other's energy.

403
00:19:57,750 --> 00:20:01,160
The fire's blazing now.

404
00:20:01,310 --> 00:20:03,160
So strong...

405
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:04,960
Come here.

406
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:14,680
Big tip for you.

407
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:16,320
Thank you.

408
00:20:17,510 --> 00:20:18,640
You too. Come here.

409
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:21,830
Lean in.

410
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:25,240
There you go.

411
00:20:25,310 --> 00:20:27,790
More tips coming.

412
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:06,790
Liu, check their backgrounds.

413
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:15,830
What's up with Xiaoqian?

414
00:21:16,510 --> 00:21:17,790
You looked panicked.

415
00:21:18,510 --> 00:21:19,440
Nothing.

416
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:21,350
Just a small issue with her shop order.

417
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:22,480
No big deal.

418
00:21:24,690 --> 00:21:25,590
That's good.

419
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:26,640
You kids

420
00:21:28,400 --> 00:21:29,960
grew up too sheltered.

421
00:21:31,440 --> 00:21:32,590
Gotta stay alert.

422
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:34,640
There are bad people out there.

423
00:21:35,510 --> 00:21:37,030
Dad, you've been saying that

424
00:21:37,030 --> 00:21:38,790
since I was little.

425
00:21:38,880 --> 00:21:40,440
I remember.

426
00:21:41,310 --> 00:21:42,150
Alright.

427
00:21:43,020 --> 00:21:44,310
No more nagging. I'm heading out.

428
00:21:44,480 --> 00:21:45,320
Take care.

429
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:56,270
(Xiaoqian)
Yimo, come to my shop.

430
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:59,070
I'm done for.

431
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:12,870
Xiaoqian.

432
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,040
What happened?

433
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:22,150
What's wrong?

434
00:22:23,350 --> 00:22:24,310
Say something.

435
00:22:24,350 --> 00:22:25,190
I'm finished.

436
00:22:25,510 --> 00:22:26,440
What happened?

437
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:27,920
Last night,

438
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:29,440
wasn't it just dinner?

439
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,160
- Eight Bamboo.
- Five Dots.

440
00:22:42,110 --> 00:22:42,950
I win.

441
00:22:49,790 --> 00:22:50,680
At first,

442
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:52,440
my luck was insane.

443
00:22:52,830 --> 00:22:53,920
I kept winning.

444
00:22:55,240 --> 00:22:57,240
I'd never had such good luck

445
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,070
at the table before.

446
00:22:59,070 --> 00:23:00,160
I really thought

447
00:23:01,790 --> 00:23:03,070
my streak had come.

448
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,240
But later, somehow,

449
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:07,200
one round

450
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:08,550
went bad.

451
00:23:08,550 --> 00:23:10,070
After that, everything went wrong.

452
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,000
I kept losing to everyone.

453
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:40,270
But at that moment,

454
00:23:40,790 --> 00:23:42,000
I'd already won a lot.

455
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:44,310
So I thought,

456
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:47,480
it was just a few bad rounds.

457
00:23:48,350 --> 00:23:49,920
My luck would come back.

458
00:23:50,350 --> 00:23:51,480
Who could've guessed...

459
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,640
I win again.

460
00:24:06,270 --> 00:24:07,110
Come on.

461
00:24:07,960 --> 00:24:08,830
Pay up.

462
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:10,550
Unbelievable.

463
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:14,550
I need to use the restroom.

464
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,640
I wanted to leave.

465
00:24:28,640 --> 00:24:30,960
But by then, I couldn't get away.

466
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:34,400
Yimo, what do I do?

467
00:24:35,960 --> 00:24:37,350
I'm really finished.

468
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:38,750
Let's call the police.

469
00:24:39,160 --> 00:24:40,720
Gambling's illegal.

470
00:24:40,720 --> 00:24:41,960
And this is gambling debt.

471
00:24:41,960 --> 00:24:43,110
Police will help.

472
00:24:43,480 --> 00:24:44,720
I'm scared.

473
00:24:45,550 --> 00:24:46,720
Even if we call the cops,

474
00:24:47,030 --> 00:24:49,000
they won't catch them all.

475
00:24:49,720 --> 00:24:51,350
What if they come after me?

476
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:53,590
Don't panic.

477
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:54,790
Let me think.

478
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:06,720
Yimo, you're all I got.

479
00:25:11,200 --> 00:25:12,960
Come with me again, okay?

480
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:14,200
He said

481
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:16,000
if the three of us sit down and talk,

482
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:17,480
there might be a way.

483
00:25:25,830 --> 00:25:26,680
Alright.

484
00:25:28,350 --> 00:25:30,160
But I need someone with us.

485
00:25:31,270 --> 00:25:32,640
I don't trust Li Xu.

486
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:34,350
Anyone's fine.

487
00:25:35,830 --> 00:25:36,790
Thank you, Yimo.

488
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:05,880
Hello, Qiang.

489
00:26:06,270 --> 00:26:07,110
You here?

490
00:26:08,240 --> 00:26:09,080
Over here.

491
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:14,270
Thank you, Qiang.

492
00:26:14,270 --> 00:26:15,680
Sorry to drag you into this.

493
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:16,520
It's fine.

494
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,270
My dad...

495
00:26:18,690 --> 00:26:20,110
I took care of things.

496
00:26:20,610 --> 00:26:21,560
I didn't tell your dad.

497
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:24,880
Thank you, Qiang.

498
00:26:41,070 --> 00:26:41,910
You're here.

499
00:26:43,030 --> 00:26:44,720
Why bring a guy?

500
00:26:46,590 --> 00:26:48,440
You don't trust me?

501
00:26:48,960 --> 00:26:49,800
Li Xu,

502
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:52,030
we were just nearby.

503
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:55,070
Xiaoqian told me about last night.

504
00:26:55,200 --> 00:26:57,000
We wanted to talk

505
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,880
and see how this can be resolved.

506
00:26:59,350 --> 00:27:00,590
She told you already?

507
00:27:03,590 --> 00:27:05,160
So do you agree or not?

508
00:27:05,240 --> 00:27:06,510
Agree to what?

509
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:08,510
You set a trap to scam her.

510
00:27:08,590 --> 00:27:09,550
What am I agreeing to?

511
00:27:10,110 --> 00:27:11,830
Careful with your words, girl.

512
00:27:11,870 --> 00:27:12,750
As you can see,

513
00:27:12,750 --> 00:27:13,920
it's just a tea room.

514
00:27:13,920 --> 00:27:14,760
A card room.

515
00:27:14,760 --> 00:27:16,640
What trap? What scam?

516
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:18,790
You know me.

517
00:27:19,070 --> 00:27:21,070
I hate scammers the most.

518
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:24,350
Right, Xiaoqian?

519
00:27:26,590 --> 00:27:28,160
Just say what you want.

520
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:30,030
How much? We'll pay.

521
00:27:30,030 --> 00:27:31,880
You make it sound easy.

522
00:27:34,350 --> 00:27:36,240
Do you know

523
00:27:36,830 --> 00:27:38,240
how much she lost last night?

524
00:27:38,640 --> 00:27:39,960
What are you paying with?

525
00:27:49,180 --> 00:27:51,340
(IOU – Borrower: Sun Xiaoqian.
Amount: 200,000)

526
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:52,350
Two hundred thousand?

527
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:55,240
How did you lose that much?

528
00:27:58,110 --> 00:27:59,720
Didn't I tell you

529
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,880
once you lose your stake, stop playing?

530
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,680
I was gone for a bit

531
00:28:04,110 --> 00:28:05,200
and you went wild?

532
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:06,680
I didn't want to gamble.

533
00:28:08,270 --> 00:28:09,960
I had already won it back.

534
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,070
I kept winning.

535
00:28:12,160 --> 00:28:14,310
I thought I wouldn't have
to borrow from you.

536
00:28:14,310 --> 00:28:15,720
Wouldn't trouble you.

537
00:28:17,310 --> 00:28:18,640
You're my friend.

538
00:28:18,750 --> 00:28:20,440
How would I mind?

539
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:21,920
The real problem now is,

540
00:28:22,270 --> 00:28:24,680
there are rules at the table.

541
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:26,070
This is getting tricky.

542
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:27,800
Li Xu.

543
00:28:29,160 --> 00:28:30,350
Please help me.

544
00:28:31,270 --> 00:28:32,110
I'm begging you.

545
00:28:32,110 --> 00:28:33,640
I can't come up with 200,000.

546
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:34,640
That's too much.

547
00:28:35,750 --> 00:28:36,960
Please?

548
00:28:37,350 --> 00:28:38,190
Okay?

549
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,000
Don't cry.

550
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:49,030
Call your best friend out.

551
00:28:50,310 --> 00:28:51,440
Let's all sit down and talk.

552
00:28:52,550 --> 00:28:53,960
Maybe there's a way.

553
00:29:01,310 --> 00:29:02,720
To be fair,

554
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:06,440
I've already done plenty.

555
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:09,240
And that money,

556
00:29:10,110 --> 00:29:11,590
she doesn't owe it to me.

557
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:14,640
The only reason I'm still helping

558
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:16,920
is I don't want to push things

559
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:18,070
too far.

560
00:29:19,070 --> 00:29:20,310
Cut the fake kindness.

561
00:29:20,500 --> 00:29:22,590
You saw Xiaoqian panic

562
00:29:22,590 --> 00:29:23,750
and set her up on purpose.

563
00:29:23,790 --> 00:29:26,790
You don't have to see me as a good guy.

564
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:29,070
But I'll say this.

565
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,960
I'm not a bad guy.

566
00:29:33,160 --> 00:29:34,000
Alright.

567
00:29:35,070 --> 00:29:36,480
Since you said that,

568
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:38,000
I'll take a step back.

569
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,720
You two stay

570
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:43,240
for dinner tonight.

571
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:45,880
We'll call it even.

572
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:46,880
In your dreams.

573
00:29:47,070 --> 00:29:48,920
Gambling's illegal.

574
00:29:49,240 --> 00:29:50,880
We're not paying a cent.

575
00:29:51,310 --> 00:29:52,270
I've called the police.

576
00:29:53,070 --> 00:29:53,910
Let's go.

577
00:29:56,070 --> 00:29:57,590
How dare you?

578
00:30:00,710 --> 00:30:01,550
Now let's see

579
00:30:01,550 --> 00:30:03,550
how you get out of here today.

580
00:30:17,510 --> 00:30:18,350
Get them.

581
00:30:25,510 --> 00:30:26,350
Yimo!

582
00:30:40,960 --> 00:30:41,800
Qiang!

583
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,480
Run. Why not?

584
00:31:10,350 --> 00:31:11,750
Tell your people to back off!

585
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:13,070
Nobody move!

586
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:15,680
Watch it.

587
00:31:15,700 --> 00:31:16,590
If you hurt me,

588
00:31:16,590 --> 00:31:17,830
I'll call the police on you.

589
00:31:21,620 --> 00:31:26,780
(Police)

590
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:36,880
Police! Help!

591
00:31:36,960 --> 00:31:38,400
He's trying to kill me!

592
00:31:38,420 --> 00:31:39,270
Help!

593
00:31:39,270 --> 00:31:40,120
Police. Don't move!

594
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:41,030
Help!

595
00:31:41,270 --> 00:31:42,110
Drop the weapon.

596
00:31:42,570 --> 00:31:43,480
Drop the knife.

597
00:31:43,590 --> 00:31:44,640
Drop it.

598
00:31:47,350 --> 00:31:48,200
Drop it, now.

599
00:31:49,750 --> 00:31:51,000
Calm down. Drop it.

600
00:31:53,200 --> 00:31:54,920
Qiang, drop it.

601
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:02,720
You can go now.

602
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:10,780
(Case Processing Area)

603
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:12,040
Xiaoqian?

604
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:21,160
You're Yimo's close friend?

605
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:25,270
You grew up together?

606
00:33:25,720 --> 00:33:26,560
Yeah.

607
00:33:28,830 --> 00:33:30,310
I've got a few more questions.

608
00:33:30,750 --> 00:33:31,750
Officer,

609
00:33:31,750 --> 00:33:34,350
I already told you everything.

610
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:35,960
I didn't hide anything.

611
00:33:41,350 --> 00:33:42,680
Sorry, Tang Tang.

612
00:33:42,720 --> 00:33:44,070
I caused trouble again.

613
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,030
I was scared something would happen.

614
00:33:46,030 --> 00:33:47,750
That's why I texted you.

615
00:33:47,750 --> 00:33:49,590
It's fine. As long as you're safe.

616
00:33:51,270 --> 00:33:52,110
Yimo.

617
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:53,800
Yimo.

618
00:33:54,270 --> 00:33:55,630
- Dad.
- You okay?

619
00:33:55,830 --> 00:33:56,670
I'm fine.

620
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:00,270
You go ahead.

621
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:03,350
Don't blame Qiang.

622
00:34:03,550 --> 00:34:05,550
I told him not to tell you.

623
00:34:05,550 --> 00:34:06,440
I was scared,

624
00:34:06,440 --> 00:34:07,920
so I asked him to come.

625
00:34:08,960 --> 00:34:09,800
I'm not blaming him.

626
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:10,960
We'll talk later.

627
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:14,320
Tang Tang saved me again today.

628
00:34:15,110 --> 00:34:18,000
Officer Tang, thank you so much.

629
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,920
You saved my daughter again.

630
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:21,840
Thank you.

631
00:34:22,550 --> 00:34:24,000
No need. Just doing my job.

632
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:25,200
See you.

633
00:34:29,630 --> 00:34:30,470
You hurt?

634
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:44,720
Yimo,

635
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:46,360
go upstairs first.

636
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:48,710
I'll say a few words to Xu Qiang.

637
00:34:50,190 --> 00:34:52,360
Dad, this was my fault.

638
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:54,000
Qiang was helping me.

639
00:34:54,400 --> 00:34:55,240
It's fine.

640
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:58,280
I'll talk business with him.

641
00:34:59,550 --> 00:35:00,390
Go home.

642
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:15,920
Qiang, thanks today.

643
00:35:16,070 --> 00:35:17,670
If my dad gives you trouble,

644
00:35:17,670 --> 00:35:19,360
tell me. I'll yell at him for you.

645
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:21,680
I'm heading up.

646
00:35:21,960 --> 00:35:22,800
Bye.

647
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:31,720
Qiang.

648
00:35:33,230 --> 00:35:34,070
Thank you

649
00:35:36,590 --> 00:35:37,480
for today.

650
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:53,880
Our families go way back.

651
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:57,510
(Police; Reception)
He claims Yimo's his biological daughter.

652
00:35:57,510 --> 00:35:58,590
But I know

653
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,510
that she's adopted.

654
00:36:01,230 --> 00:36:03,360
We don't talk about it.

655
00:36:05,230 --> 00:36:06,480
Mr. Wang treats her

656
00:36:07,110 --> 00:36:10,000
exactly like his own.

657
00:36:10,710 --> 00:36:12,590
Sometimes I envy her.

658
00:36:13,710 --> 00:36:14,840
Happy family,

659
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:16,920
great education,

660
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:18,670
and she's beautiful too.

661
00:36:19,230 --> 00:36:20,190
She has everything.

662
00:36:22,030 --> 00:36:23,710
How old was she when adopted?

663
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:28,480
Seven or eight.

664
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:30,320
When we were kids.

665
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:31,920
I don't really remember much.

666
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:34,550
Do you remember

667
00:36:34,550 --> 00:36:35,920
anything specific?

668
00:36:36,150 --> 00:36:38,360
We played and went to school together.

669
00:36:40,550 --> 00:36:41,760
When I first met her,

670
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:43,230
she barely talked.

671
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:44,760
Barely talked?

672
00:36:45,190 --> 00:36:46,960
Yeah. We got close

673
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:47,920
after a long time.

674
00:36:52,190 --> 00:36:53,670
But Yimo

675
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:58,230
is always been overly polite.

676
00:36:58,230 --> 00:36:59,480
So reserved

677
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,320
it makes me feel

678
00:37:04,230 --> 00:37:06,070
we're not that close.

679
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:25,840
Tang.

680
00:37:27,840 --> 00:37:28,880
Did you come

681
00:37:29,110 --> 00:37:30,590
because it isn't over?

682
00:37:30,590 --> 00:37:31,920
Need to go to the station?

683
00:37:32,710 --> 00:37:33,550
No.

684
00:37:33,710 --> 00:37:34,840
I'm just wondering

685
00:37:35,030 --> 00:37:36,440
if you have time.

686
00:37:37,030 --> 00:37:38,150
We could take a walk.

687
00:37:41,510 --> 00:37:43,190
Perfect timing for a late snack.

688
00:37:44,510 --> 00:37:45,400
I was gonna

689
00:37:45,400 --> 00:37:47,030
treat you someday.

690
00:37:47,110 --> 00:37:48,440
Guess you beat me to it.

691
00:37:50,280 --> 00:37:52,400
I'm not here for a thank-you meal.

692
00:37:52,550 --> 00:37:55,360
I've got a few questions.

693
00:37:56,280 --> 00:37:57,630
Ask anything.

694
00:37:57,630 --> 00:37:59,030
I'll tell you what I know.

695
00:37:59,800 --> 00:38:01,280
You've saved me twice already.

696
00:38:01,360 --> 00:38:03,150
I never got the chance to thank you.

697
00:38:03,880 --> 00:38:04,880
We're cops.

698
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:07,510
Protecting is our job.

699
00:38:07,510 --> 00:38:08,760
Don't keep thanking me.

700
00:38:09,400 --> 00:38:11,110
Still, thanks are due.

701
00:38:11,230 --> 00:38:12,150
My dad wants

702
00:38:12,150 --> 00:38:13,230
to treat you too.

703
00:38:13,710 --> 00:38:15,230
Our restaurant's really good.

704
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:17,440
I've been there

705
00:38:17,710 --> 00:38:18,760
and met your dad.

706
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:20,630
It really is good.

707
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:23,560
By the way,

708
00:38:23,590 --> 00:38:27,670
your cashier's called

709
00:38:28,190 --> 00:38:30,110
Zhang Ming?

710
00:38:30,360 --> 00:38:31,630
Yes, Ming.

711
00:38:32,510 --> 00:38:34,030
He doesn't talk much,

712
00:38:34,030 --> 00:38:35,110
but he's a good guy.

713
00:38:35,110 --> 00:38:36,360
Very attentive to customers.

714
00:38:39,630 --> 00:38:40,480
Why?

715
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,160
Nothing.

716
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:43,800
That's your turf, right?

717
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:45,710
I'm counting on you for Intel.

718
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:47,590
If you hear anything, tell me right away.

719
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,710
Yes, Officer Tang.

720
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:52,190
So where are we going?

721
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:54,440
You'll see.

722
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:55,280
Come on.

723
00:39:13,050 --> 00:39:14,220
Have you been here before?

724
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,150
Can't really remember.

725
00:39:18,840 --> 00:39:19,960
Doesn't ring a bell.

726
00:39:23,710 --> 00:39:24,630
Honestly,

727
00:39:24,840 --> 00:39:26,030
I don't know why,

728
00:39:26,030 --> 00:39:27,320
but I've forgotten

729
00:39:27,510 --> 00:39:28,880
a lot from childhood.

730
00:39:32,510 --> 00:39:33,800
Why do you care so much

731
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:34,960
whether I've been here?

732
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,440
Remember I told you

733
00:39:39,510 --> 00:39:41,030
about my best friend

734
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:42,760
from the welfare home?

735
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:44,840
The girl with the same birthmark as me?

736
00:39:47,710 --> 00:39:49,320
She wasn't just my best friend.

737
00:39:51,630 --> 00:39:53,400
She was the most important person to me.

738
00:39:55,230 --> 00:39:56,800
When I first got there,

739
00:39:57,760 --> 00:39:59,070
my parents had just passed away.

740
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:00,800
I was scared

741
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:01,920
and always getting picked on.

742
00:40:03,030 --> 00:40:05,030
Every time, she stood up for me.

743
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:08,800
We came here as kids too.

744
00:40:10,320 --> 00:40:12,000
We had no money back then.

745
00:40:13,590 --> 00:40:14,670
But I promised her

746
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:15,800
when we grew up,

747
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,920
I'd bring her on the Ferris wheel.

748
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:21,510
It's so high.

749
00:40:22,070 --> 00:40:23,800
At the top,

750
00:40:23,880 --> 00:40:25,670
you can probably see the whole city.

751
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:45,680
Thanks.

752
00:40:45,880 --> 00:40:46,720
You're welcome.

753
00:41:06,790 --> 00:41:12,280
♪Dreams of the past sleep in the chill♪

754
00:41:12,280 --> 00:41:15,730
♪Now I run toward the light♪

755
00:41:17,580 --> 00:41:22,840
♪What does the fire burn,
what does it reveal?♪

756
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:26,810
♪Is the answer found when the sun rises♪

757
00:41:27,420 --> 00:41:31,710
♪If it's all a lie♪

758
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:37,070
♪Should I tear it open?♪

759
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:43,120
♪If it's all part of the journey♪

760
00:41:43,800 --> 00:41:48,650
♪Then face the blaze head-on♪

761
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:53,510
♪Let the sun awaken my heart's crave♪

762
00:41:54,050 --> 00:41:59,780
♪Pain reminds me I'm alive♪

763
00:41:59,900 --> 00:42:04,710
♪The world can't take away every clear sky♪

764
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:10,510
♪The hotter it gets, the fiercer I fight♪

765
00:42:10,820 --> 00:42:15,540
♪Let the sun burn away all I lean upon♪

766
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:21,540
♪Leave me only what endures♪

767
00:42:21,650 --> 00:42:27,200
♪At the cliff's edge, all fear shatters♪

768
00:42:27,260 --> 00:42:34,210
♪With a grounded heart, a soul like fire♪
